            <fr:title text="Quotient of prime filters are local">Quotient of prime filters are local</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  For any filter <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on a distributive lattice <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D/F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/idem-comm-75C1/" title="Local distributive lattice" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-75C1/" display-uri="idem-comm-75C1" type="local">local</fr:link> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is prime; <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D/F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is maximal.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>7</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  By <fr:link href="/idem-comm-W57Q/" title="Prime ideals of pro-open quotient" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-W57Q/" display-uri="idem-comm-W57Q" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-W57Q/" display-uri="idem-comm-W57Q" /></fr:link>, the inverse image of the quotient <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : D \twoheadrightarrow  D/F]]></fr:tex> gives a one-to-one correspondence between prime filters in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D/F]]></fr:tex> and prime filters containing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>. This way, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D/F]]></fr:tex> is local iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{1\}]]></fr:tex> is prime, in which case <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> must be prime. The case for maximality follows from the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex> is the only distributive lattice with only one prime filter.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
